node.text:
I’m on Glennon’s podcast We Can Do Hard Things today talking about the five fights we have over and over (and over) again, how we learned to navigate our *very* different approaches to conflict, and how we realized — in the endless Groundhog Day of quarantine — that each of our separate fights are actually about THE EXACT SAME THING.  Spoiler alert: It’s not actually about the milkshake. (Even though it’s still a little about the milkshake.)
 
I love you @glennondoyle. Even when you leave a full cup of coffee in the washing machine.
 
Listen to our conversation on We Can Do Hard Things at the link in my bio.  And follow the pod so you get all the new episodes (How fun was the episode where I tried to teach G how to have fun??)
Abby

node.text:
For weeks, I’ve been behind the scenes making sure the mics are on, the headphones are plugged in, and the files are uploaded—but today, I am finally on my wife’s new podcast, We Can Do Hard Things, talking about my favorite subject: FUN.
 
All I’m looking for in life is to have fun. Glennon has no idea what fun is. So I’m having an invention with both Glennon and her sister Amanda about making time for fun, and deciding what they like to do for fun. They have no idea. 
 
My favorite part was listening to my wife talk about how she loves watching our Women’s National Team play and why it makes her so emotional. Listen through the link in my bio.
 
I think we made some progress on the fun front.
 
Hopefully, @glennondoyle will have me back soon 😉

node.text:
I joined Glennon on the We Can Do Hard Things podcast this week to talk about something incredibly personal and hard. I was surprised by how much I ended up sharing, and how healing it was for me. 
 
If you have ever experienced an inner conflict between who you are and a community, institution, family, or identity you love, or if you are still healing from the scars of being taught that who you are is wrong, or you don’t belong, I hope this conversation will be as healing for you as it was for me.
 
I never knew how much I needed to talk through this. So, thank you, Glennon, for inviting me, and thank you for inviting all of us into the messiest, hardest, most important conversations. 
Listen at the link in my bio. 
Abby

I’m on Glennon’s podcast We Can Do Hard Things today talking about the five fights we have over and over (and over) again, how we learned to navigate our *very* different approaches to conflict, and how we realized — in the endless Groundhog Day of quarantine — that each of our separate fights are actually about THE EXACT SAME THING.  Spoiler alert: It’s not actually about the milkshake. (Even though it’s still a little about the milkshake.)
 
I love you @glennondoyle. Even when you leave a full cup of coffee in the washing machine.
 
Listen to our conversation on We Can Do Hard Things at the link in my bio.  And follow the pod so you get all the new episodes (How fun was the episode where I tried to teach G how to have fun??)
Abby

Today was a day I wished for @christierampone3 for many years. As a US player we are expected to win for our country. Christie did it 5x’s. FIVE!!! She not only is a best friend but was my biggest competition every single day at practice. There is NO ONE that deserves Hall of Fame status more than you. This was a highlight of my life to be there today and to be the one to tell you that you are a legend, and now that is cemented as your legacy. I’ve always tried to be like you. Failed, of course, cause I was never reasonable during games. But my friend, I hope you celebrate this one… and I will for sure be there in October to help you put that red jacket on your shoulders. #NSHOF21 congrats to you and your whole family.

Growing up, I fought through who the world thought I should be in order to stay true to exactly who I was meant to be. 

Living in integrity with my true identity has made all the joy in my life possible — and my greatest inspiration is watching others live bravely in their integrity. 

Secret and I both believe that you shouldn’t have to sweat your identity. 

Be you. 
Be proud. 
The world is waiting for you, exactly as you are. 

Secret is helping to raise more than $4 Million for LGBTQ+ organizations. Join this support at cantcancelpride.com. 

#secretdeopartner

For weeks, I’ve been behind the scenes making sure the mics are on, the headphones are plugged in, and the files are uploaded—but today, I am finally on my wife’s new podcast, We Can Do Hard Things, talking about my favorite subject: FUN.
 
All I’m looking for in life is to have fun. Glennon has no idea what fun is. So I’m having an invention with both Glennon and her sister Amanda about making time for fun, and deciding what they like to do for fun. They have no idea. 
 
My favorite part was listening to my wife talk about how she loves watching our Women’s National Team play and why it makes her so emotional. Listen through the link in my bio.
 
I think we made some progress on the fun front.
 
Hopefully, @glennondoyle will have me back soon 😉
